# MEMORY v2 sm-memory
Full Name: Streaming Multiprocessor Local Memory System
Description:
A textual representation of memory blocks attached to an SM, suitable for deterministic parsing and canonical hashing.
Architecture Goals:
- Describe memory capacity in text
- Keep the format simple and readable
- Support auditable evolution of memory layouts
Modules:
Define module Memory Controller:
Summary: Coordinates access between compute clients and memory blocks.
Operations: arbitrate, route, protect
Inputs: requests, policy state
Outputs: grants, routed transactions
Instantiate:
Create 1 instances of Memory Controller
Memory:
Shared Memory: 256 KB
L1 Cache: 128 KB
Register Spill Buffer: 32 KB
Output: SM memory subsystem with managed local storage.
